<h1 class="inline-4c7687fdbc">How to Reach NIT Goa</h1>

<p class="inline-30aee74759">
The institute is located in Cuncolim, South Goa District, approximately 18 km from Margao city.
</p>

<h2 class="inline-fc2556a8a3">By Air</h2>

<p class="inline-30aee74759">
Dabolim Airport (GOI) is approximately 38 km from the institute (about 45 minutes by taxi).
Manohar International Airport (Mopa) is approximately 77 km away (about 1.5 hours by taxi).
Taxi services are available at both airports.
</p>

<h2 class="inline-fc2556a8a3">By Train</h2>

<p class="inline-30aee74759">
Madgaon Railway Station is approximately 15 km from NIT Goa.
Balli Railway Station is approximately 3 km from the institute.
Taxi services are available from both stations.
</p>

<h2 class="inline-fc2556a8a3">By Road</h2>

<p class="inline-30aee74759">
NIT Goa is located on National Highway 66 (NH-66) and is well connected by road to major cities including Panaji and Margao.
Visitors can reach the campus using taxis, rental cars, or local transportation.
</p>

<h1 class="inline-4c7687fdbc">About NIT Goa</h1>

<p class="inline-30aee74759">
National Institute of Technology Goa is an autonomous institute established in 2010 under the Ministry of Education, Government of India.
It has been declared an Institute of National Importance and offers undergraduate, postgraduate, and doctoral programs in engineering and technology.
</p>

